  %h3.text-black-light.xs-gamma.xs-mb0h Responsive Fonts
  %p.xs-ptb1 Font sizing is responsive - when you use one fo these font sizes, it overrides the normal font size for that element (regardless of h1, h2, etc) and uses a font size appropriate for the grid size you're operating on.
  %pre
    %code.scss
      :preserve
          The format is .<breakpoint>-<font-size> The breakpoints are as follows:
          -alpha    // largest font, 3.6rem by default
          -beta     // 3.0rem
          -gamma    // 2.4rem
          -delta    // 1.8rem
          -epsilon  // 1.4rem
          -zeta     // 1.0rem
  %p.xs-ptb1
    Some HAML examples
    %pre
      %code.haml
        :preserve
            .xs-alpha Alpha font size on all screens
            .md-gamma Gamma font size on medium screens
            .xl-alpha.md-delta.zs-epsilon
              Huge on gigantic screens
              medium on medium screens
              slightly bigger than body
              font on smallest screens
